The '''Flarestar system''',<ref name="The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons" /> was a [[Star system/Legends|star system]] located in the [[Narvath sector/Legends|Narvath sector]] of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] [[Expansion Region/Legends|Expansion Region]].<ref name="EAOC" /> It was located along the [[Gamor Run/Legends|Gamor Run]]<ref name="TEA" /> and contained a [[Star/Legends|star]] [[Orbit/Legends|orbited]] by the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Aridus/Legends|Aridus]], [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of the [[Chubbit]] [[Species/Legends|species]].<ref name="The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Flarestar system was originally created for the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] reference book ''[[The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons]]'', written by [[Daniel Wallace]], edited by [[Sue Rostoni]] and [[Steve Saffel]], and illustrated by [[Brandon McKinney]] and [[Scott Kolins]]<ref name="The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons" /> and released In [[July]] [[1998]].<ref name="TEG release date">{{RandomHouseOld|url=delrey/starwars/catalog/display.pperl?isbn=9780345420688|text=Star Wars: The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons}}</ref> ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'', a Legends reference book written by [[Jason Fry]] and [[Daniel Wallace]]<ref name="TEA" /> and released on [[August 18]], [[2009]],<ref name="TEA release date">{{PenguinRandomHouse|url=books/185066/the-essential-atlas-star-wars-by-daniel-wallace-and-jason-fry|text=The Essential Atlas: Star Wars}}</ref> identified it as the Aridus system and placed it in grid square O-14.<ref name="TEA" />

